Package: squish
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: post-quantum SSH client suite
 squish is a post-quantum SSH client suite implementing the SQSH protocol.
 .
 This package provides: sqsh (interactive client), sqsh-keygen (key
 generation), sqsh-bootstrap (trust bootstrapping), sqcp (secure copy),
 and sqftp (secure file transfer).

Package: squishd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: openssh-sftp-server
Description: post-quantum SSH server daemon
 squishd is the SQSH protocol server daemon, implementing post-quantum
 authenticated encrypted sessions.
 .
 Configuration is stored in /etc/sqsh/sqshd.toml.
